<bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
<head>Biographical Information
</head>
<p>In 1859, John Brown and a band of followers captured the federal arsenal at Harpers Ferry, but were themselves captured by Virginia forces commanded by Robert E. Lee. In 1860 the General Assembly passed several acts authorizing the payment of expenses incurred during the Harpers Ferry raid. The secretary of the commonwealth, auditor of public accounts, and adjutant general were appointed commissioners to settle accounts.</p>
</bioghist>
